parameters.name: iterable
parameters.description:
An Array or other
      iterable object
      whose elements are key-value pairs. (For example, arrays with two elements,
      such as [[ 1, 'one' ],[ 2, 'two' ]].) Each key-value pair is added to the
      new Map.

name: Map[@@species]
description: The constructor function that is used to create derived objects.
return_value: The value of the constructor (this) on which get @@species was called. The return value is used to construct copied Map instances.

name: Map.groupBy()
description: Groups the elements of a given iterable using the values returned by a provided callback function. The final returned Map uses the unique values from the test function as keys, which can be used to get the array of elements in each group.
return_value: A Map object with keys for each group, each assigned to an array containing the elements of the associated group.

parameters.name: items
parameters.description: An iterable (such as an Array) whose elements will be grouped.

parameters.name: callbackFn
parameters.description:
A function to execute for each element in the iterable. It should return a value (object or primitive) indicating the group of the current element. The function is called with the following arguments:

element

The current element being processed.

index

The index of the current element being processed.

parameters.name: index
parameters.description: The index of the current element being processed.

name: Map.prototype.constructor
description: The constructor function that created the instance object. For Map instances, the initial value is the Map constructor.

name: Map.prototype.size
description: Returns the number of key/value pairs in the Map object.

name: Map.prototype[@@toStringTag]
description: The initial value of the @@toStringTag property is the string "Map". This property is used in Object.prototype.toString().

name: Map.prototype.clear()
description: Removes all key-value pairs from the Map object.

name: Map.prototype.delete()
description:
Returns true if an element in the Map object existed and has been
      removed, or false if the element does not exist. map.has(key)
      will return false afterwards.
return_value:
true if an element in the Map object existed and has been removed, or
  false if the element does not exist.

parameters.name: key
parameters.description: The key of the element to remove from the Map object.

name: Map.prototype.entries()
description: Returns a new Iterator object that contains a two-member array of [key, value] for each element in the Map object in insertion order.

name: Map.prototype.forEach()
description: Calls callbackFn once for each key-value pair present in the Map object, in insertion order. If a thisArg parameter is provided to forEach, it will be used as the this value for each callback.

parameters.name: callbackFn
parameters.description:
A function to execute for each entry in the map. The function is called with the following arguments:

value

Value of each iteration.

key

Key of each iteration.

map

The map being iterated.

parameters.name: thisArg
parameters.description: A value to use as this when executing callbackFn.

name: Map.prototype.get()
description: Returns the value associated to the passed key, or undefined if there is none.
return_value:
The element associated with the specified key, or
  undefined if the key can't be found in the Map object.

parameters.name: key
parameters.description: The key of the element to return from the Map object.

name: Map.prototype.has()
description: Returns a boolean indicating whether a value has been associated with the passed key in the Map object or not.
return_value:
true if an element with the specified key exists in the Map object;
  otherwise false.

parameters.name: key
parameters.description: The key of the element to test for presence in the Map object.

name: Map.prototype.keys()
description: Returns a new Iterator object that contains the keys for each element in the Map object in insertion order.

name: Map.prototype.set()
description: Sets the value for the passed key in the Map object. Returns the Map object.

parameters.name: key
parameters.description: The key of the element to add to the Map object. The key may be any JavaScript type (any primitive value or any type of JavaScript object).

parameters.name: value
parameters.description: The value of the element to add to the Map object. The value may be any JavaScript type (any primitive value or any type of JavaScript object).

name: Map.prototype.values()
description: Returns a new Iterator object that contains the values for each element in the Map object in insertion order.

name: Map.prototype[@@iterator]()
description: Returns a new Iterator object that contains a two-member array of [key, value] for each element in the Map object in insertion order.
return_value: The same return value as Map.prototype.entries(): a new iterable iterator object that yields the key-value pairs of the map.
